
UPDATE product_image_scenes SET prompt_template = 'Use [PRODUCT IMAGE] as the exact source of truth for {{productName}}, preserving exact structure, scale, finish, proportions, and all product details.

CRITICAL — COMPLETE INTERIOR COMPOSITION: This is a full room interior photograph, NOT a product-only shot. The product from the reference image must be placed naturally inside a fully furnished, realistic home office. If the product is a desk, show it with a complementary office chair, a monitor or laptop, and minimal desk accessories (a pen holder, a notebook). If the product is an office chair, show it tucked under or beside a matching desk with a monitor and a desk lamp. If the product is a shelf or storage unit, show it against the wall in a room that also contains a desk and chair in the background or mid-ground. The scene must look like a real inhabited workspace — never an isolated product floating in an empty room.

CRITICAL — PROPORTIONAL SCALE RULE: Calculate the product''s real-world size as a fraction of the room width. A 160cm desk in a 5m-wide room occupies roughly 32% of the wall. A 65cm office chair spans 13% of a 5m wall. Use these proportions strictly. HUMAN SCALE ANCHOR: Imagine a 175cm adult seated at the desk (seated eye height ~120cm, shoulders at ~105cm) — the desk surface must reach their elbows (~73-76cm from floor). The office chair seat must be at ~45-52cm. A standard interior door (210cm x 90cm) visible or implied is your architectural ruler. NEVER let the product fill more than 40% of the visible wall unless its real dimensions require it. A 65cm-wide chair must NOT appear as wide as a 160cm desk.

Create a premium lifestyle interior photograph placing {{productName}} in a refined architect home office (approximately 5m x 4m, 3m ceiling) with polished concrete flooring in warm gray. Feature wall in raw board-formed concrete with subtle wood-grain imprint texture. Remaining walls in smooth warm white plaster. One large steel-framed window (2.2m x 1.8m) with slim black mullions, letting in bright natural light.

The room should feel intentional and architectural — a working space, not a showroom. The product must be integrated into a complete workspace composition with complementary furniture pieces that match the room''s aesthetic. Keep additional styling minimal: clean concrete and plaster surfaces, one slim brass desk lamp on the work surface. No random objects, no clutter — but the room must feel complete and usable.

Room palette: warm gray concrete, white plaster, black steel, warm brass accent. Modern, refined, tactile.

Lighting: bright natural daylight from the steel-framed window. Warm afternoon tone. Clean, even illumination with soft directional shadows from the window frame.

Shot with 35mm lens, eye-level, balanced composition showing the full workspace area with concrete texture visible. Architectural home office — Cereal Magazine aesthetic. Photorealistic. No text.'
WHERE scene_id = 'furniture-lifestyle-concrete-architect-office';


